      "content": "but \"accepting human limitations\" is such a soft way to put it. if the logical conclusion of the universe is total entropy and nothingness, then the most logical response to that reality is to stop participating in the friction. if the game is rigged to end in zero, then any effort put into playing is just irrational. wouldn't it be more intellectually honest to just opt out once you realize the outcome is already determined?",
